00:20:57,000 --> 00:21:02,000
 that word "again" can be translated from "above."

390
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,000
 So I think it can carry both meanings.

391
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:10,000
 What Jesus is communicating to this professional rule follower is no one can be saved

392
00:21:10,000 --> 00:21:19,000
 unless they have a second birth and are actually born from above.

393
00:21:19,000 --> 00:21:23,000
 Every person that's going to be saved has to have two births,

394
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:27,000
 a physical birth and then a spiritual birth.

395
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:28,000
 Look at how Nicodemus responds.

396
00:21:28,000 --> 00:21:32,000
 Verse 4, "Nicodemus said to him, 'How can a man be born when he's old?

397
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:36,000
 Can he enter a second time into his mother's womb and be born?'"

398
00:21:36,000 --> 00:21:43,000
 Now this isn't Nicodemus like genuinely wondering, like, "How does that work?

399
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:47,000
 Like, how do you kind of like fit up in there to like come back out?"

400
00:21:47,000 --> 00:21:51,000
 Like, that's not what is happening here.

401
00:21:51,000 --> 00:21:57,000
 This is Nicodemus, a guy who thinks he knows everything.

402
00:21:57,000 --> 00:22:01,000
 And he is responding kind of sarcastically.

403
00:22:01,000 --> 00:22:04,000
 What are you even talking about?

404
00:22:04,000 --> 00:22:08,000
 Are you talking crazy like, "Oh, you're going to climb back up in your mom

405
00:22:08,000 --> 00:22:11,000
 and then you're going to come back out."

406
00:22:11,000 --> 00:22:15,000
 But what I want you to see is his logic.

407
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:25,000
 Nicodemus is consumed with what man needs to do for God to be saved.

408
00:22:25,000 --> 00:22:30,000
 Even in his sarcastic response, "Who is all the responsibility on?"

409
00:22:30,000 --> 00:22:31,000
 It's on the man.

410
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:34,000
 "How can a man be born when he's old?

