 God is calling you to Himself tonight.

505
00:28:38,000 --> 00:28:40,000
 Tonight you're going to walk out of this place,

506
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:45,000
 and you're going to be able to say, "I showed up dead, and I left alive.

507
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:48,000
 This was a great Tuesday night."

508
00:28:48,000 --> 00:28:53,000
 [Applause]

509
00:28:53,000 --> 00:28:58,000
 Now I want you to see what Jesus says in verses 7 and 8.

510
00:28:58,000 --> 00:29:02,000
 Because what I want you to--this is where--

511
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:06,000
 Again, I'm not trying to cause unnecessary concern,

512
00:29:06,000 --> 00:29:08,000
 and yet I am trying to fight for clarity.

513
00:29:08,000 --> 00:29:12,000
 I'm trying to prompt a DTR between you and Jesus,

514
00:29:12,000 --> 00:29:16,000
 because Jesus says something very important here in verses 7 and 8

515
00:29:16,000 --> 00:29:20,000
 that has everything to do with you needing a miracle to be saved.

516
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:24,000
 Because in verse 7 He says, "Do not marvel that I said to you, 'You must be born again.'

517
00:29:24,000 --> 00:29:27,000
 The wind blows where it wishes, and you hear it sound,

518
00:29:27,000 --> 00:29:30,000
 but you do not know where it comes from or where it goes.

519
00:29:30,000 --> 00:29:32,000
 So it is with everyone who is born of the Spirit."

520
00:29:32,000 --> 00:29:34,000
 What is He saying there?

521
00:29:34,000 --> 00:29:36,000
 He's saying, "Think about the wind.

522
00:29:36,000 --> 00:29:41,000
 You can't see the wind, and yet you can hear it, and you can see its effects.

523
00:29:41,000 --> 00:29:45,000
 You can look at the trees, and you can say, 'There is wind.

524
00:29:45,000 --> 00:29:49,000
 I can't see it, but I know it is at work.'"

525
00:29:49,000 --> 00:29:54,000
 And so Jesus' point is, when a miracle takes place,

526
00:29:54,000 --> 00:30:01,000
 you can't see the Spirit, you can't even completely understand how the Spirit is working,

527
00:30:01,000 --> 00:30:08,000
 and yet you know it when a miracle has taken place, because something changes.

528
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:14,000
 So the reason that that is important is if you--

529
00:30:14,000 --> 00:30:18,000
 if God has done a miracle in your life, if He's given you new life,

530
00:30:18,000 --> 00:30:22,000
 then there should be some signs of life.

531
00:30:22,000 --> 00:30:25,000
 Like, I remember when one of our kids was born,

532
00:30:25,000 --> 00:30:28,000
 he came out of the womb, and they put him on cat,

533
00:30:28,000 --> 00:30:30,000
 and he was laying there making no sound.

534
00:30:30,000 --> 00:30:32,000
 He looked lifeless.

535
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:36,000
 Like, it was deafening silence in the delivery room.

536
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:39,000
 And then they prompted him, and he began to cry,

537
00:30:39,000 --> 00:30:41,000
 and it was the best sound that we could have heard.

538
00:30:41,000 --> 00:30:44,000
 Why? Because there were signs of life.

539
00:30:44,000 --> 00:30:49,000
 We knew that he was alive.

540
00:30:49,000 --> 00:30:54,000
 And I tell you that just to say, "Look, there's going to be times in the Christian life where you struggle.

541
00:30:54,000 --> 00:30:57,000
 There's going to be times absolutely where you have doubts.

542
00:30:57,000 --> 00:31:02,000
 There's going to be times where you might even look lifeless,

543
00:31:02,000 --> 00:31:04,000
 and you're going to come to the porch,

544
00:31:04,000 --> 00:31:12,000
 and you just need to be spurred on and kind of stimulated to go and walk closer with Jesus

545
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,000
 so that there's more signs of life."

546
00:31:14,000 --> 00:31:18,000
 But my point in telling you this is if you consider yourself a Christian

547
00:31:18,000 --> 00:31:21,000
 and you prayed a prayer once, or you raised your hair somewhere,

548
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:25,000
 or raised not your hair but your hands somewhere,

549
00:31:25,000 --> 00:31:27,000
 or you got baptized when you were an infant,

550
00:31:27,000 --> 00:31:30,000
 but you consistently look spiritually dead,

551
00:31:30,000 --> 00:31:33,000
 meaning there is no real desire to know Jesus,

552
00:31:33,000 --> 00:31:37,000
 there is no real love or appreciation for Jesus,

553
00:31:37,000 --> 00:31:40,000
 there's no real desire to learn the ways of Jesus,

554
00:31:40,000 --> 00:31:43,000
 and live life with Jesus,

555
00:31:43,000 --> 00:31:47,000
 then it is at least worth evaluating.

556
00:31:47,000 --> 00:31:51,000
 If a miracle has ever taken place.

557
00:31:51,000 --> 00:31:54,000
 I remember getting a note from a guy who trusted Christ.

558
00:31:54,000 --> 00:31:56,000
 Here's what he said.

559
00:31:56,000 --> 00:31:58,000
 He said, "I was overcome by a world of joy.

560
00:31:58,000 --> 00:32:02,000
 I found my Lord and Savior for the first time in my life.

561
00:32:02,000 --> 00:32:05,000
 I have clarity and I'm at peace.

562
00:32:05,000 --> 00:32:09,000
 God broke chains that were keeping me a prisoner to my past.

563
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:13,000
 These were chains that I thought were too strong for me or anyone else.

564
00:32:13,000 --> 00:32:15,000
 Man, I was wrong.

565
00:32:15,000 --> 00:32:18,000
 I want to spend the rest of my life serving our Lord and Savior and all that I do.

566
00:32:18,000 --> 00:32:23,000
 I want to plant the seed in others just like you and countless others did for me.

567
00:32:23,000 --> 00:32:28,000
 A fire is burning in my heart for the first time."

568
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:30,000
 Do you know what he's articulating?

569
00:32:30,000 --> 00:32:36,000
 He's just articulating, "Hey, a miracle has happened in my life.

570
00:32:36,000 --> 00:32:42,000
 Please don't hear me say that you won't struggle as a Christian.

571
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:45,000
 You will. In this world, you will have trouble."

572
00:32:45,000 --> 00:32:49,000
 And here's the other thing I want you to hear.

573
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:53,000
 You will never have to beg God to make you alive.

574
00:32:53,000 --> 00:32:55,000
 Never.

575
00:32:55,000 --> 00:32:58,000
 You'll never have to beg God to make you alive.

576
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:05,000
 If you're begging God to make you alive, you probably already are alive.

577
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:09,000
 And you should take joy in that.

578
00:33:09,000 --> 00:33:12,000
 So, three things.

579
00:33:12,000 --> 00:33:14,000
 Number one, you need more than religion to be saved.

580
00:33:14,000 --> 00:33:16,000
 Number two, you need a miracle to be saved.

581
00:33:16,000 --> 00:33:22,000
 And then number three, you need a biblical faith in Jesus to be saved.

582
00:33:22,000 --> 00:33:30,000
 You need a--and the key here is you need a biblical faith in Jesus to be saved.

583
00:33:30,000 --> 00:33:32,000
 Where do I get that from? Look with me.

584
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:35,000
 Verses 9 through 13.

585
00:33:35,000 --> 00:33:40,000
 It says, "Nicodemus said to Him, 'How can these things be?'

586
00:33:40,000 --> 00:33:44,000
 Jesus answered him, 'Are you the teacher of Israel?

587
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:46,000
 And yet you do not understand these things?

588
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:51,000
 Truly, truly, I say to you, we speak of what we know and bear witness to what we have seen,

589
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:55,000
 but you do not receive our testimony.

590
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:59,000
 If I have told you earthly things and you do not believe,

591
00:33:59,000 --> 00:34:03,000
 how can you believe if I tell you heavenly things?'"

592
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:11,000
 No one has ascended into heaven except he who descended from heaven, the Son of Man.

593
00:34:11,000 --> 00:34:15,000
 This is so powerful, guys. Don't miss what's happening here.

594
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:18,000
 Nicodemus is like, "I don't know what you're talking about."

595
00:34:18,000 --> 00:34:21,000
 And Jesus is like, "Really?

596
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:27,000
 Like, you're the one teaching the country about the kingdom of God."

597
00:34:27,000 --> 00:34:32,000
 And Jesus is saying, "Let me just tell you what has happened here."

598
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:37,000
 He says, "I am the only one," because there was this belief in Judaism

599
00:34:37,000 --> 00:34:40,000
 that some bygone saints had ascended into heaven

600
00:34:40,000 --> 00:34:44,000
 and received special insights into God's ways and plans.

601
00:34:44,000 --> 00:34:48,000
 And Jesus is like, "Look, I just want to be clear.

602
00:34:48,000 --> 00:34:56,000
 I am the only one who started out there and came down here.

603
00:34:56,000 --> 00:34:59,000
 People might leave here to go there,

604
00:34:59,000 --> 00:35:04,000
 but I'm the only one who started out there and came down to here."

605
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:08,000
 And he refers to himself as the Son of Man.

606
00:35:08,000 --> 00:35:09,000
 Do you know why that's important?

607
00:35:09,000 --> 00:35:13,000
 That's actually a reference to the Old Testament, Daniel chapter 7,

608
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,000
 and it's a reference to kingship.

609
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:19,000
 So when Jesus refers to himself as the Son of Man,

610
00:35:19,000 --> 00:35:24,000
 he's referring to himself as the king of God's kingdom.

611
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:27,000
 They're talking about how to get into the kingdom of God.

612
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:30,000
 And Demas would have been an authority on the kingdom of God.

613
00:35:30,000 --> 00:35:34,000
 And Jesus is basically saying, "Look, dude,

614
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:38,000
 the king of the kingdom is standing here telling you the truth."

615
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:41,000
 And you're like, "No, I don't know. We'll see."

616
00:35:41,000 --> 00:35:47,000
 He's like, "Something's off here. You're not getting it."

617
00:35:47,000 --> 00:35:50,000
 And he's saying, "Look, if you don't understand the elementary things

618
00:35:50,000 --> 00:35:55,000
 that I'm telling you, that you have to be born again to enter the kingdom,

619
00:35:55,000 --> 00:36:01,000
 then how in the world is your mind going to comprehend truly heavenly things?"

620
00:36:01,000 --> 00:36:04,000
 He's saying, "Look, I came from heaven.

621
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:09,000
 I know the Spirit of God because the Spirit of God and I are one.

622
00:36:09,000 --> 00:36:14,000
 I know that the Spirit of God has come to give new life to people.

623
00:36:14,000 --> 00:36:20,000
 I was there in heaven. I'm one with God. I know what's happening."

624
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:25,000
 And yet you, Nicodemus, are standing here saying, "Yeah, I don't get it."

625
00:36:25,000 --> 00:36:29,000
 And that just goes back to the first point, that a miracle has to take place.

626
00:36:29,000 --> 00:36:35,000
 I shared with you guys earlier this year that I want to become the goat

627
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:40,000
 in the 42-year-old age bracket of tennis in Richardson, Texas.

628
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:42,000
 And it's a long journey for me.

629
00:36:42,000 --> 00:36:47,000
 But when I really got back into tennis at the age of 40,

630
00:36:47,000 --> 00:36:49,000
 I started taking lessons from this person.

631
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:52,000
 I was two lessons in. I barely knew what I was doing.

632
00:36:52,000 --> 00:36:57,000
 But I then began to try and teach my 9-year-old how to play tennis.

633
00:36:57,000 --> 00:37:02,000
 And so we were in the front yard, and he started holding the racket

634
00:37:02,000 --> 00:37:05,000
 with his pointer finger along the racket.

635
00:37:05,000 --> 00:37:07,000
 And I was like, "Hey, dude, you're not holding the racket right."

636
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:10,000
 And he was like, "Yes, I am!"

637
00:37:10,000 --> 00:37:12,000
 This is what he said.

638
00:37:12,000 --> 00:37:14,000
 He's like, "I'm holding it right!" I was like, "Dude, no, you're not."

639
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:18,000
 He's like, "Yes, I am! I'm holding it right!"

640
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:22,000
 I was like, "No, dude, you're running your pointer finger along the racket."

641
00:37:22,000 --> 00:37:25,000
 He's like, "No, I'm not!"

642
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:30,000
 I was like, "Dude, I watched you do it."

643
00:37:30,000 --> 00:37:33,000
 He was like, "No, I didn't!"

644
00:37:33,000 --> 00:37:37,000
 I was like, "OK."

645
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:40,000
 And so then he hit another ball, and he did it again.

646
00:37:40,000 --> 00:37:46,000
 I was like, "Hey, hey, look! Look at your grip!"

647
00:37:46,000 --> 00:37:53,000
 And he looked down, and he goes,

648
00:37:53,000 --> 00:37:57,000
 "Oh."

649
00:37:57,000 --> 00:38:01,000
 And I was like, "You ever read the story of Nicodemus?"

650
00:38:01,000 --> 00:38:03,000
 "Not really, I didn't do that."

651
00:38:03,000 --> 00:38:08,000
 But he became a Christian right then, and it was a really powerful moment.

652
00:38:08,000 --> 00:38:10,000
 It's the same thing with Nicodemus.

653
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:15,000
 It's like, "Hey, dude, if you won't even accept what I'm teaching you

654
00:38:15,000 --> 00:38:19,000
 about how to hold a tennis racket, it doesn't get any more elementary than that.

655
00:38:19,000 --> 00:38:23,000
 If you won't accept that, how in the world are we going to begin

656
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:29,000
 to be able to talk about forehands or backhands or spin or anything like that?"

657
00:38:29,000 --> 00:38:32,000
 And it's the same thing with Nicodemus here.

658
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:39,000
 He's like, "Look, if you won't understand that at the base level,

659
00:38:39,000 --> 00:38:42,000
 you have to understand that religion will not get you there,

660
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:47,000
 and a miracle has to take place, and you're just not going to get it.

661
00:38:47,000 --> 00:38:52,000
 A miracle has to happen. Eyes have to be opened."

662
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:55,000
 And so what has to happen is you have to come to a place

663
00:38:55,000 --> 00:38:59,000
 where you realize that Jesus Christ is the King of the kingdom.

664
00:38:59,000 --> 00:39:03,000
 And what Jesus is saying is, "Look, I'm telling you the truth.

665
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:04,000
 You have to come to a place.

666
00:39:04,000 --> 00:39:07,000
 When I talk about having a biblical faith in Jesus,

667
00:39:07,000 --> 00:39:13,000
 I'm talking about coming to a place where you trust what Jesus has said.

668
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:15,000
 And you embrace it, you accept it.

669
00:39:15,000 --> 00:39:19,000
 Like, for example, Jesus declares in John 10, 30, "I and the Father are one."

670
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:23,000
 That is Jesus declaring that He is in fact God.

671
00:39:23,000 --> 00:39:28,000
 John 14, 6, Jesus says, "I am the way, the truth, and the life.

672
00:39:28,000 --> 00:39:31,000
 No one comes to the Father except through Me."

673
00:39:31,000 --> 00:39:33,000
 Do you believe that?

674
00:39:33,000 --> 00:39:37,000
 John 3, 3, "Truly I say to you, unless one is born again,

675
00:39:37,000 --> 00:39:39,000
 he can't see the kingdom of God."

676
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:41,000
 Do you believe that?

677
00:39:41,000 --> 00:39:43,000
 A biblical faith doesn't sit there and say,

678
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:46,000
 "Well, you know what, that's good for you, and that might be true for you,

679
00:39:46,000 --> 00:39:48,000
 and I might believe something different,

680
00:39:48,000 --> 00:39:51,000
 but we all, in the end, we end up at the same place."

681
00:39:51,000 --> 00:39:54,000
 No, you either believe that Jesus is the King of the kingdom,

682
00:39:54,000 --> 00:39:57,000
 which means He is the holder of truth.

683
00:39:57,000 --> 00:40:04,000
 And if He says it, it's right, or not.

684
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:11,000
 A biblical faith sees Jesus as the truth.

685
00:40:11,000 --> 00:40:20,000
 If Jesus is the truth, then to reject any of Him is to reject all of Him.

686
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
 Do you hear what I'm saying?

687
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:25,000
 To reject any of Jesus is to reject all of Him.

688
00:40:25,000 --> 00:40:27,000
 To only accept Jesus as Savior,

689
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:33,000
 but to refuse to acknowledge Him as King is to reject Jesus.

690
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:39,000
 To know Jesus as a way, but not the way, is to reject Jesus.

691
00:40:39,000 --> 00:40:43,000
 To know Jesus as a good man or a prophet,

692
00:40:43,000 --> 00:40:49,000
 but not God Himself is to reject Jesus.

693
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:52,000
 Do you know the true Jesus?

694
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:56,000
 And then look at how Jesus finishes in verses 14 and 15.

695
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:59,000
 He says, "And as Moses," this is so interesting,

696
00:40:59,000 --> 00:41:02,000
 He says, "As Moses lifted up the serpent in the wilderness,

697
00:41:02,000 --> 00:41:06,000
 so must the Son of Man be lifted up,

698
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:09,000
 that whoever believes in Him may have eternal life."

699
00:41:09,000 --> 00:41:11,000
 Here's what Jesus is doing here.

700
00:41:11,000 --> 00:41:15,000
 He's reaching back into the Old Testament in the book of Numbers

701
00:41:15,000 --> 00:41:19,000
 that I'm sure all of y'all are reading in your quiet times right now.

702
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:23,000
 Numbers 21, it's a story about the nation of Israel

703
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
 being disobedient to God,

704
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:29,000
 and God punishes them for their disobedience.

705
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:33,000
 And it's kind of this interesting story where God sends some snakes to bite Him,

706
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:37,000
 and because of the venom, people of the nation of Israel die.

707
00:41:37,000 --> 00:41:40,000
 And you might hear that and think, "Well, that's super harsh.

708
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:41,000
 That's why I can't believe in God."

709
00:41:41,000 --> 00:41:44,000
 No, you have to understand, it's not harsh.

710
00:41:44,000 --> 00:41:47,000
 It's just.

711
00:41:47,000 --> 00:41:51,000
 Because if God is holy, holy, holy, like we just sang that He is,

712
00:41:51,000 --> 00:41:56,000
 if He is perfect and right and true,

713
00:41:56,000 --> 00:42:00,000
 then to just turn a blind eye and just let people have their way

714
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:03,000
 would be unjust.

715
00:42:03,000 --> 00:42:05,000
 No, He executes justice.

716
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:08,000
 And at the same time, you know what He does?

717
00:42:08,000 --> 00:42:12,000
 He provides a means of salvation.

718
00:42:12,000 --> 00:42:19,000
 What Moses does is he erects this staff with a snake on it.

719
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:24,000
 And what God says is that if you look,

720
00:42:24,000 --> 00:42:27,000
 if you look at the staff, you will live.

721
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:28,000
 It's look and live.

722
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:31,000
 Look and live.

723
00:42:31,000 --> 00:42:36,000
 So God in His kindness, He makes provision for the venom

724
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:38,000
 that people are experiencing.

725
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:39,000
 That is our story.

726
00:42:39,000 --> 00:42:44,000
 Every single one of us has been bitten with the venom of sin.

727
00:42:44,000 --> 00:42:48,000
 The venom of sin courses through our veins.

728
00:42:48,000 --> 00:42:52,000
 And God has provided Jesus as the means for new life.

729
00:42:52,000 --> 00:42:55,000
 And His Spirit is the one who accomplishes that new life.

730
00:42:55,000 --> 00:42:58,000
 Our responsibility is to look and live.

731
00:42:58,000 --> 00:43:00,000
 What does it mean to look to Jesus?

732
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,000
 It's to come to a place.

733
00:43:01,000 --> 00:43:06,000
 A biblical faith is coming to a place where you are desperate for Jesus

734
00:43:06,000 --> 00:43:09,000
 to save you through His death, burial, and resurrection.

735
00:43:09,000 --> 00:43:10,000
 It's like this.

736
00:43:10,000 --> 00:43:13,000
 Several years ago, I went skydiving.

737
00:43:13,000 --> 00:43:17,000
 And we were doing it as skit characters for this deal here at Watermark.

738
00:43:17,000 --> 00:43:20,000
 And I was skydiving with David Penuel, a guy on staff.

739
00:43:20,000 --> 00:43:21,000
 And we were dressed up as characters.

740
00:43:21,000 --> 00:43:25,000
 We were wearing mullets, and we had taped on Fu Manchu's.

741
00:43:25,000 --> 00:43:29,000
 And I am about to jump out of the plane.

742
00:43:29,000 --> 00:43:32,000
 And right before I jump, David Penuel asks the instructors,

743
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:37,000
 "Hey, have you ever had to use the emergency parachute?"

744
00:43:37,000 --> 00:43:40,000
 And the guy was like, "Yes."

745
00:43:40,000 --> 00:43:47,000
 And I was like, "Oh, geez. Oh, man. I can't do this."

746
00:43:47,000 --> 00:43:50,000
 Here's the reality.

747
00:43:50,000 --> 00:43:57,000
 The parachute of your good works has failed.

748
00:43:57,000 --> 00:44:03,000
 The parachute of you trying to earn your way into heaven has failed.

749
00:44:03,000 --> 00:44:10,000
 The parachute of you just being a good person has failed.

750
00:44:10,000 --> 00:44:15,000
 And some of y'all are free-falling right now, and you think it's enjoyable.

751
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:18,000
 You just need to know that at the same time you're enjoying the free-fall,

752
00:44:18,000 --> 00:44:21,000
 that free-fall is leading.

753
00:44:21,000 --> 00:44:24,000
 It is a crash course toward death.

754
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:28,000
 So every single one of us desperately needs Jesus.

755
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:33,000
 To know Jesus is to know him as the only one who can save you.

756
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:38,000
 And without him, you are without hope.

757
00:44:38,000 --> 00:44:45,000
 A biblical faith is a faith that says, "Jesus, I want to live.

758
00:44:45,000 --> 00:44:52,000
 And without you, I can't. And without you, I won't."

759
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:55,000
 And so here's what I want to do.

760
00:44:55,000 --> 00:45:02,000
 I just want to end by talking to four different groups of people in this room.

761
00:45:02,000 --> 00:45:06,000
 Number one, some of y'all are here tonight, and for the first time,

762
00:45:06,000 --> 00:45:08,000
 a miracle is taking place in your life, and for the first time,

763
00:45:08,000 --> 00:45:12,000
 you've realized that religion will not cut it.

764
00:45:12,000 --> 00:45:16,000
 And you came in here, and the DTR has been clear

765
00:45:16,000 --> 00:45:19,000
 that you don't have a relationship with Jesus Christ,

766
00:45:19,000 --> 00:45:21,000
 and you want to begin a relationship with him.

767
00:45:21,000 --> 00:45:24,000
 The right response is to look to Jesus and live.

768
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:27,000
 It is to receive him as a free gift tonight.

769
00:45:27,000 --> 00:45:31,000
 Some of you here came into this place,

770
00:45:31,000 --> 00:45:34,000
 and you thought that you were a Christian,

771
00:45:34,000 --> 00:45:38,000
 and tonight you realize that you are an unsaved Christian.

772
00:45:38,000 --> 00:45:41,000
 Because the reality is that you were looking to what you've done

773
00:45:41,000 --> 00:45:45,000
 or how good you are to make you right with God.

774
00:45:45,000 --> 00:45:49,000
 If that's you, if you've realized that you are an unsaved Christian,

775
00:45:49,000 --> 00:45:54,000
 it's the same response. Receive Jesus. Look to Jesus and live.

776
00:45:54,000 --> 00:45:57,000
 Some of you here came tonight,

777
00:45:57,000 --> 00:46:00,000
 and when you think about that on a scale of one to ten,

778
00:46:00,000 --> 00:46:03,000
 how sure are you if you were to die, you'd go to heaven?

779
00:46:03,000 --> 00:46:08,000
 You always say nine because it just feels too prideful to say ten,

780
00:46:08,000 --> 00:46:10,000
 and something's just a little bit nervous in you.

781
00:46:10,000 --> 00:46:13,000
 And yet your faith is genuine.

782
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:18,000
 You've known that Jesus is your only way to a right relationship with God.

783
00:46:18,000 --> 00:46:23,000
 If that's you, my hope is that you can just rest,

784
00:46:23,000 --> 00:46:27,000
 and you can experience the joy of knowing

785
00:46:27,000 --> 00:46:32,000
 that God has done a miracle in your life.

786
00:46:32,000 --> 00:46:35,000
 Enjoy it. Be thankful for it.

787
00:46:35,000 --> 00:46:41,000
 And walk in confidence of where your relationship is.

788
00:46:41,000 --> 00:46:44,000
 And then some of you are here, and you walked in,

789
00:46:44,000 --> 00:46:46,000
 and you're like, "I'm a ten out of ten,"

790
00:46:46,000 --> 00:46:48,000
 and your faith has been strong for a long time.

791
00:46:48,000 --> 00:46:51,000
 Well, let me just ask you, when is the last time

792
00:46:51,000 --> 00:46:54,000
 that you just said thank you for the miracle

793
00:46:54,000 --> 00:46:56,000
 that God has accomplished in your life,

794
00:46:56,000 --> 00:46:58,000
 even just sitting down front during worship?

795
00:46:58,000 --> 00:47:01,000
 I was just thinking, "God, have I really embraced this talk?"

796
00:47:01,000 --> 00:47:03,000
 And so I just sat there, and I was like,

797
00:47:03,000 --> 00:47:06,000
 "God, thank you that I couldn't earn it.

798
00:47:06,000 --> 00:47:11,000
 Thank you for the miracle that you have done in my life.

799
00:47:11,000 --> 00:47:15,000
 And Jesus, I am desperate without you."

800
00:47:15,000 --> 00:47:20,000
 Let's pray together.

801
00:47:20,000 --> 00:47:23,000
 Lord, I pray that you would just have your way

802
00:47:23,000 --> 00:47:25,000
 in this room tonight,

803
00:47:25,000 --> 00:47:31,000
 that every person here would respond in some way, God.

804
00:47:31,000 --> 00:47:33,000
 And so for the people in the room

805
00:47:33,000 --> 00:47:35,000
 that want to put their trust in Jesus right now,

806
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:37,000
 then here's what I want to encourage you to do.

807
00:47:37,000 --> 00:47:39,000
 Just in the quietness of your own heart,

808
00:47:39,000 --> 00:47:44,000
 you can just say, "Lord Jesus, would you come into my life tonight?"

809
00:47:44,000 --> 00:47:46,000
 Just say, "Jesus, I receive you.

810
00:47:46,000 --> 00:47:50,000
 I receive all of you tonight."

811
00:47:50,000 --> 00:47:55,000
 Just say, "Jesus, thank you that you died on the cross for me.

812
00:47:55,000 --> 00:48:00,000
 Thank you that you rose from the dead for me.

813
00:48:00,000 --> 00:48:02,000
 Would you come into my life?

814
00:48:02,000 --> 00:48:06,000
 Would you forgive me of my sins?

815
00:48:06,000 --> 00:48:14,000
 And would you begin to lead me in a new life?"

816
00:48:14,000 --> 00:48:17,000
 And then for everyone else in the room,

817
00:48:17,000 --> 00:48:18,000
 would you just respond?

818
00:48:18,000 --> 00:48:22,000
 Respond with gratitude.

819
00:48:22,000 --> 00:48:24,000
 Praise God for the miracle he's done in your life.

820
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:28,000
 Praise God for your salvation.

821
00:48:28,000 --> 00:48:30,000
 We're going to respond with worship.

822
00:48:30,000 --> 00:48:31,000
 There's going to be people down front.

823
00:48:31,000 --> 00:48:34,000
 If you need to talk to someone, pray with someone, get more clarity,

824
00:48:34,000 --> 00:48:36,000
 there will be a team down front.

825
00:48:36,000 --> 00:48:41,000
 If after we finish, you would benefit from just some extended worship,

826
00:48:41,000 --> 00:48:44,000
 you can go up to the chapel and do that.

827
00:48:44,000 --> 00:48:46,000
 If you want to take your next step with the church,

828
00:48:46,000 --> 00:48:51,000
 whether it's through membership or finding a place to plug in, community,

829
00:48:51,000 --> 00:48:56,000
 you can go over to the loft, go to our Next Steps.

830
00:48:56,000 --> 00:49:00,000
 If you don't have a Bible, you can go out to the welcome desk.

831
00:49:00,000 --> 00:49:02,000
 We'd love to give you a copy of the Word of God.

832
00:49:02,000 --> 00:49:08,000
 But this is a time for everyone to feel the freedom to just respond.

833
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:11,000
 My hope is that you'd have clarity in this moment,

834
00:49:11,000 --> 00:49:14,000
 and that clarity would lead to confidence.

